Paladin Guild Advancement
-------------------------

Paladins rise through righteous battle. Every worthy kill earns Paladin
XP, and your guild level (1 to 15) rises automatically when you have
earned enough.

Earning Paladin XP:
- Any NPC kill where you struck the killing blow, or dealt at least a
  tenth of the victim's health, awards Paladin XP to everyone in the
  group who qualifies.
- Tougher prey is worth more; prey ten or more levels beneath you is
  worth nothing. Bosses carry large bonuses.
- Variety pays. Hunting the same spawn over and over decays the reward;
  ranging widely keeps it at full value.

Guild levels:
- Levels advance on their own the moment you have earned enough XP.
- Your guild level can never exceed your character level, and your
  combined guild levels can never exceed your character level.
- Your charisma must grow with your rank - roughly three charisma for
  every two guild levels. Guild level 15 requires charisma 22.
- Mitra grants nothing while your alignment is evil. XP earned while
  fallen is banked, and the levels pop when you atone.
- XP earned while you are held back by any of these is never lost.
- Guild level 15 is the pinnacle; Mitra's Champions join the himitra
  and lord channels.

Commands:
- 'cost' and 'advance guild' at the guild hall report your progress.
- Devotion points still come with each guild level; spend them with
  'devote'. Titles remain yours to choose via 'ptitle' and 'title'.

Your battle record survives leaving the guild. Should you return in
good standing, your guild level is restored.
